            schema:additionalType <https://data.idnau.org/pid/vocab/policy-types/data-policy> ;
            schema:description """To apply for access to our data you must be an authorised user of Dataverse.
To create an account, visit the Australian Data Archive Dataverse(Opens in a new tab/window)

.

When creating a Dataverse account, you will need to provide the following information.

    Your name (no initials).
    The name of your institution.
    A distinct username. Don’t use an email address as your username or any offensive terms, as your username may be visible to others.
    Your institutional email address in the email field. This is the email provided by your university or place of work. Generally, Australian Data Archive are not permitted to release data to commercial email addresses such as gmail.

When you submit your account creation request, Dataverse will send you an automated email with a verification link that’s valid for 24 hours. Once you’ve created your user account, please notify ada@anu.edu.au. Then you will be able to browse and search the DSS Longitudinal Studies data catalogue(Opens in a new tab/window)

.

If you’re interested in download access to any of the DSS data holdings, follow these steps.

    Find the dataset you would like to access.
    Select Request access
    Complete the online request form.
    You will need to confirm that you have read and will abide by the DSS Longitudinal Studies Data Access and Use Guidelines(Opens in a new tab/window)

.
Email a signed copy of the Confidentiality Deed Poll(Opens in a new tab/window)
to LongitudinalStudies@dss.gov.au and ada@anu.edu.au. """ ;
            schema:name "Longitudinal Studies Data Access and Use Guidelines V5.0" ;
            schema:url "https://ada.edu.au/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Longitudinal-Studies-Data-Access-and-Use-Guidelines-V5.0.pdf"^^xsd:anyURI ;
        ] ;
